      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This is a valid concern, as allowing exemptions can create unequal treatment under the law and undermine the principle of equal protection. The state's duty to protect the rights of all citizens generally outweighs the rights of a specific group, even if those rights are rooted in religious beliefs. The failure to uphold universal laws can also be seen as discriminatory, as it prioritizes one subset of believers above others.",
